        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(qwen): bound video description success response reads",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\n`describeQwenVideo` in `extensions/qwen/media-understanding-provider.ts` reads the **success** video-description response with an unbounded `await res.json()`. The Qwen OpenAI-compatible endpoint is untrusted external input; a hostile or misconfigured `baseUrl` can stream an arbitrarily large JSON body with no byte ceiling, buffering the whole payload into memory before parse — a memory-pressure / hang (OOM) vector on the media-understanding path.\n\n## Evidence\n\nReuses the shared bounded reader `readProviderJsonResponse` (16 MiB cap, cancels the stream on overflow) — same pattern as the recently merged #95218 / #96027 / #96038. Plugin-scoped, no new abstraction. Note: malformed JSON is now normalized to a stable `Qwen video description failed: malformed JSON response` (previously a raw `SyntaxError`); the OpenAI-compatible payload extraction is unchanged.\n\nReal behavior proof (live vitest, not mocked): a real `ReadableStream` streaming a 64 MiB body is fed to the exported function, asserting `Qwen video description failed: JSON response exceeds 16777216 bytes` is thrown, `wasCanceled() === true`, `readCount < 64`; plus a malformed-JSON regression and the normal payload case.\n\n```\nTests  3 passed (3)\n```\n",
        "branch": "fix/bound-qwen-video",
